At the height of {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro|ja|藤原仲麻呂|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara no Nakamaro|qq=}}’s power, Otokoroe’s grandson, {{ill|Murakuni Shimasu|ja|村国島主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Shimasu|qq=}}, initially entered Nakamaro’s service, and the clan enjoyed his patronage. Just before the {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion|ja|藤原仲麻呂の乱|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion|qq=}} in the 8th year of the {{ill|Tenpyō-hōji era|ja|天平宝字|1=Tenpyō-hōji|2=ja|3=天平宝字|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpyō-hōji era|qq=}} ({{ill|764|ja|764th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/764|qq=}}), Shimasu held the position of {{ill|Shōyaku|ja|少掾|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōyaku|qq=}} in Mino, {{ill|Murakuni Koro|ja|村国子老|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Koro|qq=}} served as the governor ({{ill|Kokushi|ja|国司|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokushi|qq=}}) of {{ill|Noto Province|ja|能登国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Noto Province|qq=}}, and {{ill|Murakuni Mushi-maro|ja|村国虫麻呂|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Mushi-maro|qq=}} held the post of secretary ({{ill|Kaisei|ja|介|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaisei|qq=}}) in {{ill|Echizen Province|ja|越前国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Echizen Province|qq=}}. This distribution of posts appears to have been part of Nakamaro’s plan to mobilize military forces from eastern and northern regions centered on {{ill|Omi Province|ja|近江国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omi Province|qq=}}, but his failure to raise an army and subsequent defeat meant that the plan never came to fruition. Shimasu was killed by an envoy sent to secure the fortification at {{ill|Fuwa Barrier|ja|不破関|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuwa Barrier|qq=}}, and the other two lost their gubernatorial appointments. Later, the Imperial Court exonerated Murakuni Shimasu. Although Koro and Mushi-maro, who had once fallen from power, later returned to serve at the same Rank as before, their descendants were unable to maintain their status.
Much later, a woman named {{ill|Murakuni Kazuko|ja|村国数子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Kazuko|qq=}}, who worked in the Imperial harem, reached the Rank of external {{ill|Ju-go-i Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ju-go-i Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in the 17th year of the {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgan|qq=}} era ({{ill|875|ja|875th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/875|qq=}}); she was the last member of the Murakuni Clan to attain the 5th Rank. Subsequently, the names of {{ill|Murakuni Gyōse|ja|村国業世|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Gyōse|qq=}} (of the upper {{ill|Shōroku|ja|正六位|1=Senior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōroku|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}}) and his son {{ill|Murakuni Harusawa|ja|村国春沢|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Harusawa|qq=}} appear in the "Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku" in the 4th clause of the 1st year of the {{ill|Ninwa|ja|仁和|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninwa|qq=}} era ({{ill|885|ja|885th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/885|qq=}}).
