[[ja:%E6%9D%91%E5%9B%BD%E6%B0%8F]] [[sn:Murakuni Clan]] [[en:Murakuni Clan]]

'''Murakuni Clan''' ({{ill|Murakuni Clan|ja|村国氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Clan|qq=}}, Murakuni-ji) is a family that flourished as regional magnates and central officials in {{ill|Japan|ja|日本|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan|qq=}} from the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asuka period|qq=}} to the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara period|qq=}}. Their hereditary title ({{ill|Kabane|ja|カバネ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabane|qq=}}) is {{ill|Ren|ja|連|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ren|qq=}}. Their stronghold was in {{ill|Mino Province|ja|美濃国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mino Province|qq=}}, {{ill|Kagami District|ja|各務郡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagami District|qq=}}, and after {{ill|Murakuni Otokoroe|ja|村国男依|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Otokoroe|qq=}} distinguished himself during the {{ill|Jinshin War|ja|壬申の乱|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jinshin War|qq=}} in {{ill|672|ja|672年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/672|qq=}}, they went on to produce mid-level officials. In the 760s they were patronized by {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro|ja|藤原仲麻呂|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara no Nakamaro|qq=}}, but this association led to their decline after the {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion|ja|藤原仲麻呂の乱|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion|qq=}} in {{ill|764|ja|764年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/764|qq=}}.
