At the height of [[:en:Fujiwara no Nakamaro|Fujiwara no Nakamaro]]’s power, Otokoroe’s grandson, {{ill|Murakuni Shimasu|ja|村国島主|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Shimasu|qq=}}, initially entered Nakamaro’s service, and the clan enjoyed his patronage. Just before the [[:en:Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion|Fujiwara no Nakamaro Rebellion]] in the 8th year of the [[:en:Tenpyō-hōji|Tenpyō-hōji]] ([[:en:764|764]]), Shimasu held the position of {{ill|Shōyaku|ja|少掾|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōyaku|qq=}} in Mino, {{ill|Murakuni Koro|ja|村国子老|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Koro|qq=}} served as the governor ([[:en:Kokushi (official)|Kokushi]]) of [[:en:Noto Province|Noto Province]], and {{ill|Murakuni Mushi-maro|ja|村国虫麻呂|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Mushi-maro|qq=}} held the post of secretary ({{ill|Kaisei|ja|介|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaisei|qq=}}) in [[:en:Echizen Province|Echizen Province]]. This distribution of posts appears to have been part of Nakamaro’s plan to mobilize military forces from eastern and northern regions centered on [[:en:Ōmi Province|Omi Province]], but his failure to raise an army and subsequent defeat meant that the plan never came to fruition. Shimasu was killed by an envoy sent to secure the fortification at {{ill|Fuwa Barrier|ja|不破関|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuwa Barrier|qq=}}, and the other two lost their gubernatorial appointments. Later, the Imperial Court exonerated Murakuni Shimasu. Although Koro and Mushi-maro, who had once fallen from power, later returned to serve at the same Rank as before, their descendants were unable to maintain their status.
Much later, a woman named {{ill|Murakuni Kazuko|ja|村国数子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Kazuko|qq=}}, who worked in the Imperial harem, reached the Rank of external {{ill|Ju-go-i Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ju-go-i Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in the 17th year of the [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan]] era ([[:en:875|875]]); she was the last member of the Murakuni Clan to attain the 5th Rank. Subsequently, the names of {{ill|Murakuni Gyōse|ja|村国業世|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Gyōse|qq=}} (of the upper {{ill|Shōroku|ja|正六位|1=Senior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōroku|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}}) and his son {{ill|Murakuni Harusawa|ja|村国春沢|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakuni Harusawa|qq=}} appear in the "Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku" in the 4th clause of the 1st year of the [[:en:Ninna|Ninwa]] era ([[:en:885|885]]).
